WEBVTT

00:10.397 --> 00:12.097
♪ (CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

00:12.164 --> 00:13.431
JOHN WILSON:
<i>Hey, New York.</i>

00:15.331 --> 00:16.798
<i>There are</i>
<i>countless opportunities</i>

00:16.864 --> 00:19.297
<i>to make small talk</i>
<i>in a big city.</i>

00:19.364 --> 00:23.064
<i>Even though some people</i>
<i>seem to avoid it at all costs.</i>

00:24.831 --> 00:27.197
<i>Small talk is the glue</i>
<i>that binds us all together</i>

00:27.864 --> 00:29.164
<i>and the armor that shields us</i>

00:29.230 --> 00:30.964
<i>from each other's</i>
<i>darkest thoughts.</i>

00:32.431 --> 00:34.597
<i>It's useful when you meet up</i>
<i>with a friend...</i>

00:35.464 --> 00:37.197
<i>go on a date...</i>

00:37.264 --> 00:40.431
<i>or try to start</i>
<i>a professional relationship.</i>

00:42.531 --> 00:44.464
<i>Failing to know</i>
<i>how to engage properly</i>

00:44.531 --> 00:48.030
<i>could condemn you to a life</i>
<i>of social alienation.</i>

00:48.097 --> 00:49.898
<i>But it can be</i>
<i>extremely rewarding</i>

00:49.964 --> 00:51.664
<i>if you know how to do it right.</i>

00:52.898 --> 00:55.497
<i>So instead of making people</i>
<i>take on the full weight</i>

00:55.564 --> 00:57.731
<i>of all your problems,</i>

00:57.798 --> 00:59.531
<i>stick with me,</i>
<i>and I'll make sure</i>

00:59.597 --> 01:02.164
<i>that every talk you have</i>
<i>from here on out</i>

01:02.230 --> 01:03.664
<i>is small talk.</i>

01:04.564 --> 01:06.497
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

01:07.698 --> 01:09.664
♪ (QUIET MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

01:09.731 --> 01:12.798
JOHN: <i>A nice way to begin</i>
<i>is by leaving your apartment</i>

01:12.864 --> 01:15.798
<i>and trying to find someone</i>
<i>who is willing to talk to you.</i>

01:16.597 --> 01:18.030
(CLEARS THROAT)

01:18.097 --> 01:20.931
<i>Thankfully, New York is filled</i>
<i>with friendly people,</i>

01:20.997 --> 01:22.898
<i>so this should be easy.</i>

01:24.731 --> 01:26.664
<i>One of the main functions</i>
<i>of small talk</i>

01:26.731 --> 01:29.864
<i>is to fill space</i>
<i>with polite conversation,</i>

01:29.931 --> 01:32.497
<i>uh, until</i>
<i>you can be alone again.</i>

01:32.564 --> 01:36.664
<i>So make sure to only talk about</i>
<i>stuff from your everyday life</i>

01:36.731 --> 01:41.197
<i>that anyone can relate to</i>
<i>and forget about easily.</i>

01:41.264 --> 01:43.631
<i>You can talk about</i>
<i>how nice the weather is,</i>

01:43.698 --> 01:45.264
<i>uh, but just make sure that</i>

01:45.331 --> 01:47.397
<i>you never mention</i>
<i>climate change.</i>

01:49.097 --> 01:51.230
<i>You can talk about what's on TV,</i>

01:51.297 --> 01:53.798
<i>uh, but make sure</i>
<i>that you only talk--</i>

01:53.864 --> 01:56.731
<i>you only mention, uh,</i>
<i>the nice stuff.</i>

01:56.798 --> 01:59.464
<i>You can also talk about</i>
<i>the health of your plant,</i>

01:59.531 --> 02:01.664
<i>but don't mention that</i>
<i>it's a painful reminder</i>

02:01.731 --> 02:04.331
<i>of your ex, uh,</i>
<i>who gave it to you,</i>

02:04.397 --> 02:06.130
<i>uh, because she loved you</i>

02:06.197 --> 02:08.931
<i>even though you were</i>
<i>emotionally unavailable,</i>

02:08.997 --> 02:09.997
<i>uh, to her.</i>

02:12.397 --> 02:15.230
<i>Pets are, uh, really good</i>
<i>to talk about too.</i>

02:15.297 --> 02:16.597
<i>You can always talk about pets.</i>

02:17.664 --> 02:19.497
<i>But much like in real estate,</i>

02:19.564 --> 02:23.364
<i>uh, location is everything</i>
<i>when you're making small talk.</i>

02:24.431 --> 02:25.798
<i>You could pose the same question</i>

02:25.864 --> 02:28.130
<i>in two, uh,</i>
<i>different environments</i>

02:28.197 --> 02:30.798
<i>and receive</i>
<i>wildly different answers.</i>

02:30.864 --> 02:33.197
<i>You could ask a question</i>
<i>to a philosopher...</i>

02:33.264 --> 02:35.664
Do you think mankind
is gonna make a comeback?

02:36.997 --> 02:38.264
I hope so. (SIGHS)

02:38.331 --> 02:42.731
Um, if we can survive the perils
of climate change, inequality,

02:42.798 --> 02:46.597
and, um, the fantastic
weapons of destruction

02:46.664 --> 02:48.364
we've created for ourselves.

02:48.431 --> 02:49.864
JOHN: <i>But that same question,</i>

02:49.931 --> 02:52.798
<i>uh, might get a much different</i>
<i>answer at WrestleMania.</i>

02:52.864 --> 02:55.230
Do you think Mankind
is gonna make a comeback?

02:55.297 --> 02:56.731
No, not today.

02:56.798 --> 02:58.964
He fell off too many
Hell in a Cells.

02:59.030 --> 03:00.964
-JOHN: Oh, really?
-Yeah.

03:01.030 --> 03:03.331
JOHN: What about mankind
in general?

03:03.397 --> 03:06.130
Oh! Mankind, like,
the whole world?

03:06.197 --> 03:08.064
I mean, it's not bad,
it could be better,

03:08.130 --> 03:09.898
but I'm happy with my life, so.

03:10.898 --> 03:12.798
JOHN: What do you, uh,
what do you do?

03:12.864 --> 03:15.030
Uh, I catch child predators.

03:15.097 --> 03:18.297
If you wanna look me up,
it's Mr. 17540 on Facebook.

03:18.364 --> 03:20.464
That's what I do
in my spare time.

03:20.531 --> 03:21.831
JOHN: You catch child predators?

03:21.898 --> 03:23.798
-Yes, I do.
-JOHN: How?

03:23.864 --> 03:26.731
I set up the stings online,
and I Facebook Live 'em,

03:26.798 --> 03:28.030
and I go and get 'em.

03:28.097 --> 03:30.064
-JOHN: Really?
-Yes, sir.

03:30.130 --> 03:31.898
JOHN: <i>At the end</i>
<i>of our conversation,</i>

03:31.964 --> 03:33.931
<i>the gentleman invited me</i>
<i>to his headquarters</i>

03:33.997 --> 03:35.497
<i>-in Pennsylvania.</i>
-♪ (SYNTH MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

03:35.564 --> 03:37.030
<i>And I figured</i>
<i>I could learn something</i>

03:37.097 --> 03:39.230
<i>by heading out there</i>
<i>to see him in action.</i>

03:40.831 --> 03:42.731
So, what's going on today?

03:42.798 --> 03:45.164
Well, we're gonna go catch us
a predator today.

03:45.230 --> 03:47.431
JOHN: Yeah?
Do you have something set up?

03:47.497 --> 03:49.698
Oh, yeah, a guy's 28 years old,

03:49.764 --> 03:51.297
he knows that I'm 15,

03:51.364 --> 03:52.831
and told him to bring condoms,

03:52.898 --> 03:55.731
and he's gonna try to meet me
for sex.

03:55.798 --> 03:58.230
JOHN: <i>Because his job involves</i>
<i>keeping people engaged</i>

03:58.297 --> 03:59.997
<i>for long periods of time,</i>

04:00.064 --> 04:01.864
<i>I figured he would have</i>
<i>some insight</i>

04:01.931 --> 04:04.397
<i>into sustaining</i>
<i>friendly conversations.</i>

04:05.297 --> 04:06.531
(CELL PHONE DINGS)

04:06.597 --> 04:08.997
JOHN: So, what are you saying
to this person right now?

04:09.064 --> 04:10.531
So, he just told me...

04:11.331 --> 04:12.898
Like I said, I find these guys,

04:12.964 --> 04:14.531
I look at their profile,
I ask 'em questions.

04:14.597 --> 04:17.564
I-- I said I liked his dogs.
He said, "Thank you."

04:17.631 --> 04:19.264
Right away, he says,

04:19.331 --> 04:21.831
"It's a Norwegian elkhound
and a chocolate Lab,"

04:21.898 --> 04:23.764
and "What are you doing
on here, then?"

04:23.831 --> 04:25.397
Because I told him I'm 15.

04:27.764 --> 04:29.931
We'll tell him
I'm just looking for fun

04:29.997 --> 04:33.097
and that my grandma
used to have dogs like that.

04:33.164 --> 04:34.964
JOHN: Did your grandma
really have dogs like that?

04:35.030 --> 04:36.030
No, hell no.

04:37.230 --> 04:39.264
JOHN: <i>It seems like</i>
<i>when you're having small talk,</i>

04:39.331 --> 04:42.130
<i>it's okay to lie</i>
<i>if it helps you avoid</i>

04:42.197 --> 04:44.297
<i>uh, getting too personal,</i>

04:44.364 --> 04:46.664
<i>because that can be</i>
<i>a real turn off.</i>

04:46.731 --> 04:50.164
You know, I've had people
just vent their problems

04:50.230 --> 04:53.164
like, "My mother-in-law
is in the hospital,"

04:53.230 --> 04:55.064
or "My girlfriend
just cheated on me,"

04:55.130 --> 04:56.497
and those are
the people, like, I--

04:56.564 --> 04:58.664
Well, I'm not here
for a conversation like that.

04:58.731 --> 05:01.931
And I just block 'em
and go to the next one.

05:01.997 --> 05:03.997
JOHN: <i>But in the middle</i>
<i>of our conversation,</i>

05:04.064 --> 05:05.297
<i>his plans fell through.</i>

05:05.631 --> 05:07.331
Damn it!

05:07.397 --> 05:10.064
Now he's saying
he doesn't wanna do it,

05:10.130 --> 05:12.798
and he's bailing out
at the last second.

05:14.531 --> 05:15.997
Like, the best I can say
is like,

05:16.064 --> 05:17.764
"Okay, thanks
for wasting my day.

05:17.831 --> 05:19.230
I took school off today."

05:21.931 --> 05:25.197
JOHN: <i>So, I guess try not</i>
<i>to say too much,</i>

05:25.264 --> 05:27.064
<i>or else you might scare</i>
<i>someone away.</i>

05:28.064 --> 05:30.631
<i>Because the more you talk</i>
<i>to someone,</i>

05:30.698 --> 05:33.297
<i>the harder it is to hide</i>
<i>who you really are.</i>

05:37.264 --> 05:40.130
<i>I got a rug</i>
<i>off Craigslist recently.</i>

05:40.197 --> 05:43.497
<i>The ad said that there were</i>
<i>a few blood stains on the rug</i>

05:43.564 --> 05:46.097
<i>from a stress-related incident.</i>

05:46.164 --> 05:47.597
<i>Uh, but it was free.</i>

05:48.631 --> 05:51.030
<i>When I got to the storage space</i>
<i>to pick it up,</i>

05:51.097 --> 05:53.731
<i>instead of the small talk</i>
<i>about interior decorating</i>

05:53.798 --> 05:56.297
<i>that I expected,</i>
<i>the guy just spent</i>

05:56.364 --> 05:58.831
<i>the entire time</i>
<i>telling me about his divorce.</i>

06:12.297 --> 06:13.964
JOHN: <i>It can be hard</i>
<i>to keep a conversation</i>

06:14.030 --> 06:16.030
<i>in a safe zone</i>

06:16.097 --> 06:18.497
<i>when you're filled</i>
<i>with so much pain.</i>

06:18.564 --> 06:22.764
RUG GUY: My ex-wife demanded
I get rid of my shit.

06:23.497 --> 06:24.831
JOHN: <i>But an expert small talker</i>

06:24.898 --> 06:26.664
<i>will know how to</i>
<i>suppress these emotions</i>

06:26.731 --> 06:28.364
<i>and appear stable,</i>

06:28.431 --> 06:31.230
<i>no matter how much pressure</i>
<i>is building up inside.</i>

06:32.631 --> 06:35.164
<i>For example, if you need to</i>
<i>retrieve a sweater</i>

06:35.230 --> 06:37.698
<i>from someone</i>
<i>that you used to date, uh,</i>

06:37.764 --> 06:40.431
<i>start first by sending them</i>
<i>a text message.</i>

06:40.497 --> 06:44.264
<i>And if you discover that</i>
<i>they had deleted your number,</i>

06:44.331 --> 06:48.431
<i>uh, just calmly remind them, uh,</i>
<i>of your name.</i>

06:48.497 --> 06:51.030
<i>It might have been a while</i>
<i>since you've seen them,</i>

06:51.097 --> 06:52.764
<i>so when you go</i>
<i>to their apartment</i>

06:52.831 --> 06:53.931
<i>to pick it up,</i>

06:53.997 --> 06:56.030
<i>make sure</i>
<i>to keep the conversation light</i>

06:56.097 --> 06:57.898
<i>and focused on the sweater.</i>

06:58.564 --> 07:00.597
<i>Which should be easy for you</i>

07:00.664 --> 07:03.798
<i>because, uh, before you stopped</i>
<i>seeing each other,</i>

07:03.864 --> 07:06.364
<i>uh, she-- she told you that</i>
<i>you were too closed off.</i>

07:07.564 --> 07:10.531
<i>And when she brings up</i>
<i>that she's dating someone new,</i>

07:10.597 --> 07:12.764
<i>uh, just, uh, wish her well</i>

07:12.831 --> 07:15.431
<i>and bike home</i>
<i>as quickly as possible.</i>

07:16.664 --> 07:18.731
<i>If-- if you do want to talk</i>
<i>to someone</i>

07:18.798 --> 07:21.030
<i>about your previous</i>
<i>relationships,</i>

07:21.097 --> 07:24.230
<i>you should only do it</i>
<i>with your really close friends,</i>

07:24.297 --> 07:28.030
<i>who you can call up anytime</i>
<i>to reminisce.</i>

07:28.097 --> 07:30.097
FRANCIS: (OVER PHONE) <i>I don't</i>
<i>know if we've ever talked</i>

07:30.164 --> 07:32.264
<i>about any of our exes</i>
<i>with each other.</i>

07:32.331 --> 07:35.164
(LAUGHING) <i>I don't know...</i>

07:35.664 --> 07:36.731
JOHN: Okay.

07:36.798 --> 07:39.130
FRANCIS: <i>I don't know if</i>
<i>you and I have ever, uh,</i>

07:39.864 --> 07:41.798
<i>bro-ed down like that.</i>

07:41.864 --> 07:43.531
JOHN: <i>You-- I guess</i>
<i>you don't always need</i>

07:43.597 --> 07:45.097
<i>to talk about personal stuff,</i>

07:45.164 --> 07:47.230
<i>uh, for someone to technically</i>
<i>be your friend.</i>

07:48.230 --> 07:49.497
♪ (SOFT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

07:49.564 --> 07:51.798
<i>And if you're not a big talker</i>
<i>in general,</i>

07:51.864 --> 07:54.264
<i>you can use a popular technique</i>
<i>called baiting</i>

07:54.331 --> 07:56.164
<i>to get people to talk to you.</i>

07:57.431 --> 08:00.130
<i>Uh, baiting involves</i>
<i>wearing or doing something</i>

08:00.197 --> 08:03.130
<i>that will invite conversation.</i>

08:03.197 --> 08:07.997
<i>This could be a fashion choice</i>
<i>or a method of transportation.</i>

08:08.898 --> 08:10.097
<i>The way you move,</i>

08:10.798 --> 08:11.931
<i>the way you eat.</i>

08:12.798 --> 08:14.964
<i>A new haircut is good bait.</i>

08:15.030 --> 08:17.431
<i>Or you can just</i>
<i>dress like a hose.</i>

08:20.297 --> 08:22.631
<i>Wearing a band T-shirt</i>
<i>is a popular way</i>

08:22.698 --> 08:24.831
<i>to get someone to talk to you</i>
<i>in public.</i>

08:24.898 --> 08:26.764
<i>But if you can't afford</i>
<i>to go to, um,</i>

08:26.831 --> 08:28.264
<i>a Blue Chip concert,</i>

08:28.331 --> 08:30.230
<i>you can always go see</i>
<i>a cover band</i>

08:30.297 --> 08:34.564
<i>that has a name that's similar</i>
<i>to a, uh, a real band.</i>

08:34.631 --> 08:38.264
-♪ (BAGPIPE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
-(CHEERING)

08:38.331 --> 08:41.197
JOHN: <i>Once you've seen enough,</i>
<i>sprint over to the merch table</i>

08:41.264 --> 08:43.130
<i>to, uh, beat the crowd</i>

08:43.197 --> 08:46.831
<i>and pick out the boldest apparel</i>
<i>that you can afford.</i>

08:46.898 --> 08:48.698
<i>Then you're gonna go</i>
<i>to the tallest elevator</i>

08:48.764 --> 08:51.230
<i>in your city, uh,</i>
<i>and it won't be long</i>

08:51.297 --> 08:53.230
<i>until someone takes the bait</i>

08:53.297 --> 08:55.164
<i>and starts a conversation</i>
<i>with you.</i>

08:55.230 --> 08:56.164
ELEVATOR WOMAN:

08:56.230 --> 08:57.431
JOHN: Have you heard of them?

08:59.731 --> 09:00.864
JOHN: Yeah, they're bagpipers.

09:00.931 --> 09:01.864
ELEVATOR WOMAN:

09:01.931 --> 09:03.064
JOHN: They're a bagpipe
cover band.

09:03.130 --> 09:05.531
ELEVATOR WOMAN:

09:05.597 --> 09:07.831
JOHN: <i>Once you have</i>
<i>enough small talk with someone,</i>

09:07.898 --> 09:10.030
<i>they will eventually become</i>
<i>an acquaintance.</i>

09:11.497 --> 09:13.230
<i>To be a successful acquaintance,</i>

09:13.297 --> 09:15.664
<i>you will need to have, uh,</i>
<i>broad interests</i>

09:15.731 --> 09:18.397
<i>and, uh, relatable flaws.</i>

09:18.464 --> 09:21.297
<i>And no matter how awful</i>
<i>your life currently is,</i>

09:21.364 --> 09:24.497
<i>you can never reveal this</i>
<i>to another acquaintance.</i>

09:24.564 --> 09:27.497
<i>So it requires a bit</i>
<i>of camouflage.</i>

09:28.664 --> 09:31.230
<i>You want to seem like someone</i>
<i>who is busy,</i>

09:31.297 --> 09:34.397
<i>but also likes to relax.</i>

09:34.464 --> 09:37.664
<i>That's why going on vacation</i>
<i>will give you enough ammunition</i>

09:37.731 --> 09:40.631
<i>for years' worth of, uh,</i>
<i>encounters.</i>

09:40.698 --> 09:42.731
<i>So just go to a travel agency</i>

09:42.798 --> 09:46.698
<i>and ask what the most popular</i>
<i>destinations are.</i>

09:46.764 --> 09:50.631
I can send you to Punta Cana,
Cancún, Jamaica.

09:50.698 --> 09:53.597
Any of those places
will be my places to go to.

09:53.664 --> 09:55.030
JOHN: Cancún?

09:55.097 --> 09:56.397
Cancún sounds good.

09:56.464 --> 09:58.197
It's just one person
in the room?

09:58.264 --> 10:00.597
Or are you going to be sharing
the room with someone else?

10:00.664 --> 10:03.331
-JOHN: No, it's just me.
-Okay.

10:03.397 --> 10:04.764
JOHN: <i>And if your travel agent</i>

10:04.831 --> 10:06.931
<i>starts talking</i>
<i>about relationships,</i>

10:06.997 --> 10:08.631
<i>uh, don't reciprocate,</i>

10:08.698 --> 10:11.531
<i>and just wait</i>
<i>for the transaction to complete.</i>

10:11.597 --> 10:13.297
-TRAVEL AGENT: Eighty-six?
-JOHN: Yeah.

10:13.364 --> 10:15.097
TRAVEL AGENT:
I got married in that year.

10:15.164 --> 10:18.397
Don't wanna remember that
too much. (LAUGHS)

10:18.464 --> 10:20.297
-JOHN: Uh--
-I was married for 20 years.

10:21.030 --> 10:22.130
JOHN: Okay.

10:22.197 --> 10:25.497
Relationships, you know,
they start, they end.

10:25.564 --> 10:29.264
So I think, uh,
love cannot be forever.

10:29.331 --> 10:33.097
Relationships are not forever,
and I'm-- I'm okay with it.

10:33.164 --> 10:36.064
I'm, you know, if-- if I find
someone else, great,

10:36.130 --> 10:37.898
I'm not looking, but hey,
if he comes along,

10:37.964 --> 10:40.431
let's see who can deal with me.
'Cause I'm not that easy.

10:40.731 --> 10:41.864
But hey.

10:41.931 --> 10:43.698
Would I marry
the same type of person again?

10:43.764 --> 10:46.364
No. But at that point,
I wanted to? Yes.

10:46.431 --> 10:47.964
And did I have fun? Yes.

10:48.698 --> 10:50.197
Could I have done better? Yes.

10:50.997 --> 10:52.497
But that's what's coming next.

10:52.564 --> 10:54.631
So let's see what happens.
I'll let you know.

10:54.698 --> 10:56.431
-JOHN: Thank you.
-You're welcome.

10:56.497 --> 10:58.798
-JOHN: I appreciate it.
-No problem.

10:58.864 --> 11:02.064
JOHN: <i>It's hard to understand</i>
