had a pet that died?

24:21.297 --> 24:22.698
When I was a kid, yeah.

24:22.764 --> 24:24.030
JOHN: What was that pet?

24:24.097 --> 24:25.331
His name was Lucky.

24:26.764 --> 24:29.164
He wasn't so lucky, though.
He got hit by a car.

24:30.364 --> 24:32.898
-JOHN: He got hit by a car?
-Yeah, I was a little boy, man.

24:39.597 --> 24:40.731
JOHN: Um...

24:42.764 --> 24:45.898
I, uh, I used to have a cat,

24:45.964 --> 24:48.264
when I was growing up,
called-- named Fluffy,

24:49.831 --> 24:50.831
and she died.

24:50.898 --> 24:51.864
That sucks, bro.

24:51.931 --> 24:53.698
That's what happens.
That's life, though...

24:54.997 --> 24:56.397
unfortunately.

24:58.397 --> 25:00.331
JOHN: I also had
a friend that died recently.

25:02.331 --> 25:04.130
He was in, like, a car accident.

25:04.197 --> 25:05.364
That's terrible.

25:06.264 --> 25:07.497
JOHN: Uh...

25:09.864 --> 25:12.431
and that was really hard.

25:12.497 --> 25:15.397
Yeah, I feel your pain,
trust me.

25:17.130 --> 25:18.331
JOHN: Um...

25:19.297 --> 25:20.964
Yo, is this true?
Is this for real?

25:21.030 --> 25:23.230
-JOHN: Yeah.
-I'm sorry, bro.

25:24.597 --> 25:26.531
My-- my friend
just killed himself,

25:26.597 --> 25:27.764
before I came here.

25:28.631 --> 25:30.597
-JOHN: Before you came here?
-Well...

25:31.997 --> 25:33.564
about 30 days before.

25:34.664 --> 25:38.731
Probably low-key why I--
why I am out here, you know?

25:38.798 --> 25:41.230
Whether I know it or not,
I think that the universe

25:41.297 --> 25:43.164
just put me here,
I don't really know.

25:43.230 --> 25:45.164
I feel like I really needed
to get away.

25:51.164 --> 25:54.230
-JOHN: That's really heavy.
-Yeah, it's brutal.

25:54.297 --> 25:56.531
It's my first close friend
I ever really lost.

26:08.631 --> 26:09.997
(CAN CRINKLING)

26:14.631 --> 26:15.997
So, do you like New York?

26:17.230 --> 26:19.197
(LAUGHS)

26:21.030 --> 26:24.230
♪ (MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

26:30.230 --> 26:32.431
JOHN: <i>I returned to New York</i>
<i>the next day,</i>

26:32.497 --> 26:35.397
<i>and it was nice to be back home</i>
<i>in my element.</i>

26:36.531 --> 26:39.297
<i>Although, I'm not sure</i>
<i>I could ever look at my city</i>

26:39.364 --> 26:41.097
<i>the same way again.</i>

26:42.764 --> 26:44.397
<i>The world is full of people</i>

26:44.464 --> 26:46.997
<i>that need to get something</i>
<i>off their chest.</i>

26:47.064 --> 26:50.097
<i>And even though it can be risky</i>
<i>to open up,</i>

26:50.164 --> 26:52.997
<i>it's worth it</i>
<i>when you find the right person.</i>

26:54.364 --> 26:58.731
<i>Otherwise, stuff will just</i>
<i>keep, uh, building up,</i>

26:58.798 --> 27:02.431
<i>and you need to sift out</i>
<i>all that bad stuff</i>

27:02.497 --> 27:04.130
<i>uh, once in a while.</i>

27:04.197 --> 27:07.731
<i>And, uh, then you'll--</i>
<i>you'll be in a better place.</i>

27:07.798 --> 27:10.097
<i>And, uh,</i>
<i>once you take care of that,</i>

27:10.164 --> 27:12.864
<i>you'll finally be able to return</i>

27:12.964 --> 27:15.864
<i>to a blissful world</i>
<i>of small talk.</i>

27:19.531 --> 27:21.030
<i>This is John Wilson.</i>

27:21.097 --> 27:22.397
<i>Thanks for watching.</i>

27:23.130 --> 27:26.564
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

28:15.097 --> 28:16.798
♪ (SOOTHING MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

28:26.664 --> 28:27.698
JOHN WILSON:
<i>I even met someone</i>

28:27.764 --> 28:30.364
<i>who used scaffolding</i>
<i>on a romantic date.</i>

28:30.431 --> 28:32.164
You left me outside
when it rained.

28:32.931 --> 28:34.097
That was interesting.

28:34.497 --> 28:36.297
♪ (MUSIC CONTINUES) ♪
